      <tr><td>15</td><td>I can read and evaluate an argumentative text, identifying thesis, evidence, and conclusion.</td><td>Interpretive Reading</td></tr>
      <tr><td>16</td><td>I can use advanced discourse markers to argue, qualify, and organize extended speech.</td><td>Presentational Speaking</td></tr>
      <tr><td>17</td><td>I can describe and compare cultural values and practices across communities.</td><td>Cultures (Practices / Perspectives)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p class="exit-profile"><strong>Exit profile:</strong> The learner communicates with confidence on personal and social topics, uses the subjunctive to nuance discourse, and begins exploring abstract and hypothetical thought.</p>
</section>

